subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax.
Pronotum yellow, underside of prothorax, meso- and metathorax black throughout. Pronotal width 
1.8–2.5 mm
(mean 
2.04 mm
), ratio pronotal length: width 0.45–0.53 (mean 0.50). Elytral length 4.6–6.0 mm (mean 
5.35 mm
), maximal elytral width in the middle of elytra of 3.2–4.0 mm (mean 
3.56 mm
), elytra broad with ratio maximal width: length 0.62–0.72 (mean 0.66). Elytra yellow, apical quarter or at least apical margin brownish red to red (
Figure 24
). Males with short elytral ridges beyond scutellum and long elytral ridges from humerus to the apical third of elytra (
Figure 24A
). Scutellum, coxae, and trochantera black; femora, tibiae, and tarsi yellow.

Female genitalia.
Cornu of spermatheca slightly bent at apex, middle part broad, nodulus large (
Figure 26
). Bursa sclerites large, usually with five strong spines (
Figure 25
).

Male genitalia.
Median lobe slender, round in cross-section, slightly narrowed in the middle (
Figure 27A
), apex slightly carinate ventrally (
Figure 27B
). Tectum very long, slender, not lanceolate, deeply incised at apex (
Figure 27A
). Endophallic spiculae slender, all slightly bent dorsally in lateral view (
Figure 27B
). Ventral pair shortest, slightly curved inwards, middle pair longest, nearly straight, dorsal pair slightly curved inwards. Sac structure pointed apically, orifice nearly circular.
